<item>
            <title>[LU-8006] Specify ordering of TBF policy rules</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-8006</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;In the documentation it states &quot; Whenever a queue is newly created, it goes though the rule list and takes the first matched rule as its rule, so that the queue knows its RPC token rate.&quot;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;How does it the order the rules? Is it in the order they were created?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We want 2 initial sets of NID groups, &apos;Login&apos; and &apos;compute&apos;. But the compute nodes&apos; NIDs are not uniquely different from the login nodes. But if we can order the rules we can list the login nodes first and then compute.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
